♪ GOD ERASE MY PITIFUL PAST

04:31.836 --> 04:35.797
[LAUGHING AND CHATTING]

04:44.066 --> 04:46.111
-BE CAREFUL!

04:48.940 --> 04:50.290
OH, MY GOD!

04:51.465 --> 04:52.553
-AAH!

04:52.683 --> 04:55.730
-[CHAOTIC SHOUTING]

04:55.860 --> 04:57.166
-MY LEG!

04:57.297 --> 04:58.907
-LET'S GO, LET'S GO!

04:59.037 --> 05:00.909
COME ON, WE'LL GO
GET HELP! WE'LL GO GET HELP!

05:01.039 --> 05:02.432
-YEAH, HURRY UP!
-DON'T WORRY!

05:09.221 --> 05:11.223
-OUT ON THE JETTY,
SOMEONE'S HURT!

05:11.354 --> 05:13.138
-STOP!

05:13.269 --> 05:15.140
HELP!

05:15.271 --> 05:16.272
STOP!

05:16.403 --> 05:18.100
-SIR, YOU'VE GOTTA HELP US.

05:18.230 --> 05:20.145
MY FRIEND'S CAUGHT OUT ON
THE JETTY, AND HE'S GONNA DROWN.

05:20.276 --> 05:21.669
COME ON!

05:21.799 --> 05:23.279
-WE GOT AN EMERGENCY AT
THE JETTY OFF TOWER 18.

05:23.410 --> 05:24.976
I NEED BACKUP RIGHT AWAY.

05:49.261 --> 05:50.872
GET EVERYBODY AWAY FROM HIM
ONTO THE BEACH!

05:51.002 --> 05:52.569
OFF THE JETTY, ON THE BEACH! GO!

05:59.968 --> 06:03.188
-[SIRENS APPROACHING]

06:26.255 --> 06:27.387
-NEWMIE!

06:31.391 --> 06:33.784
-GIRLS, GET BACK TO THE BEACH.
GET OFF THE JETTY.

06:33.915 --> 06:35.395
-LET'S GET YOU OUT OF HERE.

06:36.396 --> 06:37.962
OKAY, WE GOTTA MOVE
THIS BOULDER.

06:38.093 --> 06:39.573
I THINK IT'S BROKEN HIS LEG.
-ALL RIGHT.

06:39.703 --> 06:41.575
-TAKE IT EASY.
WE'LL GET YOU OUT OF HERE.

06:46.188 --> 06:47.407
ALL RIGHT, GET OVER HERE.
RIGHT HERE.

06:48.408 --> 06:49.409
-WE GOTTA PULL THE ROCK OFF.

06:49.539 --> 06:51.585
-ALL RIGHT, ON THREE.

06:51.715 --> 06:54.762
-ONE, TWO, THREE!

06:54.892 --> 06:57.373
-[GRUNTING]

06:58.374 --> 06:59.506
-ONE, TWO, THREE!

07:03.074 --> 07:04.772
OKAY, ONE, TWO...

07:04.902 --> 07:06.774
-PUT YOUR BACK INTO IT!
-THREE!

07:15.957 --> 07:18.742
ALL RIGHT, HE'S OUT.
HE'S OUT!

07:20.788 --> 07:21.963
-PUT YOUR HANDS ON MY ARM!

07:22.093 --> 07:23.268
-HERE WE GO, COME ON!

07:23.399 --> 07:25.227
ON THREE.
ONE, TWO, THREE!

07:29.840 --> 07:31.102
WATCH YOUR STEP,
WATCH YOUR STEP!

07:31.233 --> 07:32.582
EASY ON THE LEG.

07:32.713 --> 07:34.323
COME ON GUYS, HERE WE GO
-EASY.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.281
-THIS WAY. COME ON.
I GOT YOU.

07:36.412 --> 07:38.588
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT.

07:38.719 --> 07:39.850
HERE WE GO.

07:51.079 --> 07:52.384
WATCH HIS HEAD.
WATCH HIS HEAD.
-HERE WE GO.

07:52.515 --> 07:53.385
WATCH THAT LEG.

07:54.082 --> 07:55.213
EASY DOWN.

07:55.344 --> 07:56.171
-ARGH!

07:56.301 --> 07:57.172
-ALL RIGHT.

07:59.435 --> 08:00.610
GET HIM TO THE HOSPITAL.

08:01.176 --> 08:02.220
-OKAY.

08:02.960 --> 08:05.746
-YOU SEE THAT?
YOU SEE WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOUR FRIEND?

08:05.876 --> 08:08.139
THAT'S A REAL GOOD REASON
NOT TO DRINK BEER ON THE BEACH.

08:08.270 --> 08:09.489
BESIDES THAT,
YOU'RE ALL UNDERAGE.

08:10.402 --> 08:11.621
ALL RIGHT. SHOWTIME'S OVER.

08:12.317 --> 08:14.668
GO ON. EVERYBODY OFF THE JETTY.

08:20.804 --> 08:21.631
-THINK HE'LL BE OKAY?

08:22.545 --> 08:23.981
-YEAH, HE'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

08:24.721 --> 08:26.549
WON'T BE DOING ANY ROCK CLIMBING
FOR A WHILE.

08:27.898 --> 08:28.725
COME ON, PAL.

08:29.726 --> 08:32.207
-[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS]

08:52.532 --> 08:54.577
-SPLIT THE BIKE BATH
ON THE LEFT UP THERE.

08:54.708 --> 08:56.840
-OKAY, NINE A.M. TOMORROW
MORNING, RIGHT?

08:56.971 --> 08:57.885
BYE-BYE.

08:58.929 --> 09:00.235
-HEY, YOU GOT A SECOND?

09:01.062 --> 09:03.499
-FOR YOU? ANY TIME, ANYWHERE.

09:03.630 --> 09:04.544
-I NEED A FAVOR.

09:05.283 --> 09:06.807
WILL YOU TEACH ME
HOW TO SURF?

09:07.459 --> 09:11.159
-AREN'T YOU THE ONE
WHO USED TO CALL SURFERS
"MACHO CRETINS"?

09:11.289 --> 09:12.943
THAT WAS BEFORE
I MOVED IN WITH ONE.

09:13.074 --> 09:14.162
-A-HA!

09:14.684 --> 09:16.033
AND NOW YOU'VE GOT
A CHANGE OF HEART?

09:16.773 --> 09:18.949
-EDDIE IS ALWAYS SAYING THAT
WE ONLY DO WHAT I LIKE TO DO.

09:19.080 --> 09:20.777
SO, I JUST FIGURED THAT
IT'S TIME TO SHUT HIM UP.

09:20.908 --> 09:22.649
-THAT'S GOOD. HAHA.

09:22.779 --> 09:24.738
SHAUNI, I'M A LITTLE RUSTY.

09:24.868 --> 09:27.610
-MITCH SAYS THAT YOU ARE
THE BEST LONGBOARDER
HE HAS EVER SEEN.

09:28.872 --> 09:30.439
-WELL, IN MY PRIME,

09:30.570 --> 09:32.484
I GUESS YOU COULD SAY
I WAS RIGHT UP THERE.

09:32.615 --> 09:33.921
-JUST ONE LESSON?

09:34.922 --> 09:35.792
JUST FOR OLD TIME'S SAKE?

09:36.967 --> 09:38.316
-YOU'VE TWISTED MY ARM.

09:40.101 --> 09:42.059
-WHEN CAN WE DO IT?

09:42.190 --> 09:44.192
-TOMORROW AFTERNOON,
FOUR O'CLOCK, DOCKWEILER BEACH.
BE THERE.

09:44.322 --> 09:45.323
-I SHALL.

09:46.890 --> 09:47.761
DEFINITELY.

09:52.809 --> 09:54.463
-WHAT TIME'S KAYE
COMING OVER?

09:54.594 --> 09:57.335
-SIX O'CLOCK.
AND NO COOKIES OR CANDY
BEFORE DINNER.

09:57.466 --> 09:59.773
-I WON'T. I WOULDN'T WANT
TO SPOIL MY APPETITE.

09:59.903 --> 10:01.383
-OH, GIVE ME A BREAK.

10:01.513 --> 10:02.863
YOU'RE ALWAYS SNEAKING
SWEETS BEFORE DINNER.

10:02.993 --> 10:04.168
GIVE ME THAT.
-ONLY WHEN YOU'RE COOKING.

10:05.213 --> 10:06.431
-WAIT A MINUTE.

10:06.954 --> 10:09.434
YOU DELIBERATELY SPOIL
YOUR APPETITE WHEN I COOK?

10:09.565 --> 10:10.871
-WHAT DIFFERENCE DOES IT MAKE?

10:11.001 --> 10:12.916
YOUR FOOD SPOILS IT ANYWAY.

10:13.047 --> 10:14.439
-FUNNY. VERY FUNNY.

10:14.570 --> 10:16.354
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
I GOTTA GO GET MY FINS.

10:16.485 --> 10:17.355
-OKEY-DOKE.

10:19.357 --> 10:20.315
-HEY, BEACH BOY.

10:23.144 --> 10:24.058
BEEN A LONG TIME.

10:25.929 --> 10:27.148
-NOT LONG ENOUGH.

10:28.236 --> 10:29.716
-IS THAT ANY WAY
TO GREET AN OLD FRIEND?

10:29.846 --> 10:31.892
-WE'RE NOT FRIENDS, SATO.
WE NEVER WERE.

10:32.588 --> 10:34.590
-WELL, MAYBE WE CAN BE.

10:34.721 --> 10:37.419
THAT IS, IF YOU HAVE TIME
FOR ME, WHAT WITH YOUR HERO'S
JOB AND YOUR SON.

10:37.549 --> 10:38.420
-ALL RIGHT, WHAT THE HELL
DO YOU WANT?

10:39.203 --> 10:40.117
-WHAT DO I WANT?

10:41.162 --> 10:43.338
HOW ABOUT FIVE YEARS
OF MY LIFE BACK.

10:43.468 --> 10:45.427
-HEY, MAN, YOU GOT YOURSELF
TO BLAME FOR GOING TO PRISON,
NOT ME.

10:47.298 --> 10:48.343
-THAT'S JUST IT.

10:48.473 --> 10:49.605
I DO BLAME YOU.

10:50.432 --> 10:52.608
YOU OWE ME,
AND I'M HERE TO COLLECT.

10:58.092 --> 10:58.919
HANDSOME BOY.

10:59.920 --> 11:02.139
-HOBIE, GET IN THE CAR.

11:02.270 --> 11:03.184
-SURE.
-GO ON.

11:18.025 --> 11:19.374
-SEE YOU 'ROUND,
BEACH BOY.

11:31.603 --> 11:32.909
-HOW ABOUT SOME DESSERT?

11:33.780 --> 11:34.737
-YEAH.

11:34.868 --> 11:35.651
-YEAH?
-OF COURSE.

11:35.782 --> 11:37.348
-OKAY. EXCUSE ME.

11:37.914 --> 11:38.959
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

11:41.309 --> 11:43.093
-WHY DO YOU ALWAYS TALK
WITH YOUR MOUTH FULL?

11:43.833 --> 11:45.487
-SORRY.
-[PHONE RINGS]

11:49.273 --> 11:50.405
-CAN I TEMPT YOU?

11:51.145 --> 11:51.972
-MAYBE LATER.

11:57.629 --> 11:58.500
HELLO?

11:59.501 --> 12:02.243
I HOPE I'M NOT INTERRUPTING
YOUR COZY DINNER, BEACH BOY.

12:09.946 --> 12:12.166
-[PHONE RINGS]

12:16.866 --> 12:17.867
-AREN'T YOU GONNA
ANSWER IT?

12:17.998 --> 12:19.695
-UM, IT'S A WRONG NUMBER.

12:20.304 --> 12:21.828
-HOW DO YOU KNOW?
-NO, SIT DOWN, SIT DOWN.

12:21.958 --> 12:23.133
JUST HAVE SOME DESSERT.

12:23.264 --> 12:24.918
I'LL GET IT. EXCUSE ME.

12:30.706 --> 12:31.663
WHAT?

12:33.491 --> 12:36.451
-THIS IS THE SECOND TIME TODAY
THAT YOU REJECTED MY ATTEMPT
AT FRIENDSHIP.

12:37.713 --> 12:40.324
BUT YOUR LADY FRIEND COULD BE
A WHOLE LOT FRIENDLIER.

12:40.455 --> 12:42.936
-DON'T CALL HERE AGAIN.
IF YOU DO, I'LL--

12:43.545 --> 12:44.459
-YOU'LL WHAT?

12:45.460 --> 12:46.548
-JUST DON'T.

13:12.922 --> 13:15.185
-YOU KNOW, KAYE, THAT DINNER
LAST NIGHT WAS SO GOOD,

13:16.186 --> 13:18.362
THAT ME AND DAD WANT TO TREAT
YOU TO SOMETHING SPECIAL.

13:18.493 --> 13:21.365
-TARO BURGERS!
-TARO BURGERS!

13:21.496 --> 13:22.932
-[LAUGHING]
-ALL RIGHT.

13:24.804 --> 13:25.979
WAIT 'TILL YOU TRY IT.

13:41.995 --> 13:43.605
-MARTINI.

13:45.433 --> 13:46.390
-HI.

13:51.134 --> 13:52.744
-OUR TABLE'S READY.
-OKAY.

14:15.028 --> 14:17.247
-UH, I'LL BE RIGHT BACK, OKAY?

14:27.301 --> 14:29.085
-HEY, BEACH BOY.

14:29.216 --> 14:31.131
I THINK MY FRIEND WANTS
TO BUY ME A DRINK.

14:31.261 --> 14:33.742
-GIVE HIM HIS CHECK.
HE'S LEAVING.

14:34.438 --> 14:36.397
-I THINK YOU'RE BEGINNING
TO SWEAT, BEACH BOY.

14:37.311 --> 14:39.139
BEEN OUT IN THE SUN TOO LONG.
YOU BETTER COOL OFF.

14:39.269 --> 14:40.357
BEER.

14:41.793 --> 14:44.100
-LOOK, I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE AFTER OR WHAT
YOU'RE TRYING TO PROVE,

14:44.231 --> 14:45.580
BUT YOU BETTER BACK OFF.

14:47.190 --> 14:48.452
-YOU'RE STILL SWEATING.

14:49.627 --> 14:53.370
I SWEAT IN A ROTTEN,
STINKING PRISON CELL
FOR FIVE YEARS.

14:53.501 --> 14:55.242
WANTED TO KILL YOU
FOR EVERYTHING YOU DID TO ME.

14:56.069 --> 14:57.766
BUT DON'T WORRY, BEACH BOY.

14:57.897 --> 14:59.768
I DON'T WANT TO KILL YOU
ANYMORE, THAT WOULD BE TOO EASY.

15:00.638 --> 15:01.683
-YOU KNOW YOU'RE SICK?

15:08.820 --> 15:12.085
-LOST MY BUSINESS AND EVERYTHING
I HAD BECAUSE OF YOU.

15:13.651 --> 15:17.133
BET YOU DIDN'T EVEN KNOW I HAD
A WIFE AND KID. THE OPERATIVE
WORD BEING "HAD."

15:17.264 --> 15:18.830
AFTER YOUR HEROICS,
SHE LEFT ME.

15:18.961 --> 15:20.136
TOOK MY KID WITH HER.

15:20.963 --> 15:22.791
SAID I WASN'T FIT
TO BE A FATHER.

15:22.922 --> 15:24.749
-WHY ARE YOU BLAMING ME
FOR ALL THIS?

15:24.880 --> 15:26.186
-IT'S NOT JUST YOU.

15:27.317 --> 15:28.666
I BLAME MY EX-WIFE, TOO.

15:29.754 --> 15:31.060
WHAT'S LEFT OF HER.

15:33.845 --> 15:35.238
SHE WAS A BEAUTIFUL WOMAN,

15:35.369 --> 15:36.848
BUT SHE WON'T BE WORKING
AS A MODEL ANYMORE.

15:37.849 --> 15:40.287
I INTRODUCED HER TO A BLADE,
AND YOU KNOW WHAT, BEACH BOY?

15:41.505 --> 15:43.986
SHE JUST DOESN'T PHOTOGRAPH
THE WAY SHE USED TO.

15:44.117 --> 15:45.770
-ALL RIGHT, YOU LISTEN TO ME!

15:47.163 --> 15:48.208
YOU STAY AWAY FROM ME.

15:49.296 --> 15:50.775
AND YOU STAY AWAY
FROM MY SON.

15:53.691 --> 15:56.085
-[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS]

16:05.573 --> 16:07.096
-DAD, WHO WAS THAT GUY?

16:07.227 --> 16:09.185
-OH, HE'S JUST A...

16:10.534 --> 16:11.709
HE'S JUST A FRIEND OF MINE.

16:12.884 --> 16:13.842
BURGERS HERE YET?

16:13.973 --> 16:15.887
-NOPE. DOES IT LOOK LIKE IT?

16:16.018 --> 16:17.541
-[LAUGHING]

16:38.954 --> 16:40.825
-SHAUNI!
-HI.

16:41.522 --> 16:45.091
WHEW. I AM EXHAUSTED ALREADY
FROM CARRYING THIS STUFF.

16:45.221 --> 16:47.919
-WHAT'D YOU DO? YOU BUY OUT
A LOCAL SURF SHOP?

16:48.050 --> 16:49.878
-WELL, YOU KNOW,
I LIKE TO BE PREPARED.

16:50.009 --> 16:53.534
-SOMETIMES IT AMAZES ME
HOW THIS SPORT HAS CHANGED.

16:53.664 --> 16:54.665
NOW, LOOK AT THAT SURFBOARD.

16:55.275 --> 16:57.451
SO SMALL YOU CAN HARDLY
STAND ON IT.

16:57.581 --> 17:02.108
DO YOU KNOW THAT MY FIRST BOARD
WAS A 10-FOOT PLANK THAT WEIGHED
80 POUNDS?

17:02.238 --> 17:05.154
-WHOA.
-YEAH. WE DIDN'T HAVE
ANY WET SUITS.

17:06.415 --> 17:09.723
WE HAD THE BOARD AND THE WAVE.
THAT'S ALL WE NEEDED.

17:12.683 --> 17:14.685
I WISH YOU'D HAVE BEEN THERE
TO SEE THAT, SHAUNI.

17:23.259 --> 17:24.304
HEAVEN ON EARTH.

17:25.218 --> 17:28.438
-[MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYS]

17:32.660 --> 17:36.011
♪ PICTURES FLOATING IN MY MIND

17:36.533 --> 17:41.930
♪ OF DAYS SPENT SWIMMING UNDER MOONSHINE ♪

17:42.061 --> 17:46.587
♪ CARRIED NOTHING BUT OUR PRIDE

17:46.717 --> 17:52.680
♪ HELD UP HIGH OVER THE OCEAN TIDES

17:54.986 --> 17:59.208
♪ THOSE WERE BETTER DAYS

17:59.339 --> 18:03.299
♪ WAVES CRASHED THROUGH THE BLAZE

18:03.430 --> 18:05.954
♪ GOOD OLD BOYS CATCHING RAYS

18:06.085 --> 18:10.306
♪ THOSE WERE GOLDEN, BETTER DAYS

18:25.974 --> 18:29.760
♪ WAKING UP BEFORE THE DAWN

18:29.891 --> 18:33.112
♪ THE COAST WAS OUR FRONT LAWN

18:33.242 --> 18:36.811
♪ UNDER THE SUN

18:39.205 --> 18:42.947
♪ THOUGH THE YEARS HAVE SLIPPED AWAY

18:43.078 --> 18:48.562
♪ WE WILL ALWAYS KNOW WE DID IT OUR WAY

18:51.826 --> 18:55.917
♪ THOSE WERE BETTER DAYS

18:56.047 --> 18:59.616
♪ WAVES CRASHED THROUGH THE BLAZE

18:59.747 --> 19:02.576
♪ GOOD OLD BOYS OUT CATCHING RAYS

19:02.706 --> 19:06.580
♪ AND THOSE WERE GOLDEN, BETTER DAYS

19:30.647 --> 19:32.214
♪ AH, BETTER DAYS

19:32.345 --> 19:35.957
♪ WERE NOTHING SHORT OF PERFECT PRAISE

19:36.087 --> 19:39.265
♪ LEAVING NOTHING LEFT TO SAY

19:39.395 --> 19:42.746
♪ AND THOSE WERE GOLDEN, BETTER DAYS

20:18.956 --> 20:21.742
-SIX YEARS AGO,
I WAS WORKING A TOWER
IN THE MARINA.

20:22.264 --> 20:24.179
SATO HAD A SHIPPING COMPANY.

20:24.310 --> 20:25.702
-YEAH, I REMEMBER.
IT WAS A COVER FOR
HIS DRUG OPERATION.

20:25.833 --> 20:27.704
-RIGHT.

20:27.835 --> 20:29.271
WELL, I STUMBLED ON
SOME EVIDENCE THAT WOULD
CONVICT HIM.

20:29.837 --> 20:31.055
HE TRIED TO BUY ME OFF.

20:31.186 --> 20:33.362
WHEN I REFUSED,
HE LOST IT.

20:33.493 --> 20:35.146
HE MADE A RUN FOR IT,
HE DAMN NEAR KILLED A COP
WITH HIS BARE HANDS

20:35.277 --> 20:36.713
BEFORE I CAUGHT HIM.

20:36.844 --> 20:38.237
-WELL, HE'S KEEPING
HIS NOSE CLEAN SO FAR.

20:38.367 --> 20:39.847
HE'S ALREADY REGISTERED
WITH HIS PAROLE OFFICER.

20:40.630 --> 20:42.502
-HE TOLD ME HE SLASHED
HIS WIFE'S FACE.

20:42.632 --> 20:43.503
-THOSE WERE HIS WORDS?

20:44.112 --> 20:45.940
-WELL, NOT EXACTLY,
BUT HE IMPLIED IT.

20:46.593 --> 20:48.072
-THAT'S YOUR INTERPRETATION.

20:48.203 --> 20:49.552
UNLESS HIS WIFE
FILES A COMPLAINT--

20:49.683 --> 20:51.467
WHY DON'T YOU TRACK HER DOWN
AND TALK TO HER?

20:51.598 --> 20:54.078
-I MEAN, AT LEAST LOOK AT HER FACE?
-I WILL DO WHAT I CAN, MITCH.

20:54.209 --> 20:56.864
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT THIS GUY'S CAPABLE OF?

20:58.474 --> 21:01.303
-AS MUCH AS I'D LIKE TO,
I CAN'T ARREST A MAN FOR
WHAT HE'S CAPABLE OF.

22:50.281 --> 22:52.849
-[DOG BARKING]

23:58.959 --> 24:02.179
-OKAY, ONE MORE RIDE,
ON YOUR OWN THIS TIME.
THEN THAT'S IT.

24:05.922 --> 24:07.446
HAVE FUN. BE CAREFUL.

24:11.841 --> 24:13.060
GOOD STUFF, HOBIE.
SEE YOU LATER.

24:32.079 --> 24:34.081
-HEY, YOU'VE GOTTEN GOOD
SINCE THE LAST TIME
I SAW YOU.

24:34.211 --> 24:35.996
-WHEN WAS THAT?

24:36.126 --> 24:37.954
-OH, A LONG TIME AGO.
I'M AN OLD FRIEND
OF YOUR DAD'S.

24:38.085 --> 24:40.827
-OH, YEAH. I SAW YOU AT
THE RESTAURANT TALKING
TO MY DAD YESTERDAY.

24:41.567 --> 24:44.134
I'M GOING OVER TO SEE HIM
IF YOU WANT TO COME.

24:44.265 --> 24:45.396
-UNDER ONE CONDITION.

24:46.310 --> 24:48.095
SHOW ME HOW TO DO ONE
OF THOSE TURNS OUT IN THE WATER?

24:48.225 --> 24:49.879
-YOU MEAN A 360?
-YEAH.

24:50.010 --> 24:51.011
-SURE. COME ON.

24:51.141 --> 24:52.142
-GOT AN EXTRA BOARD?

24:52.273 --> 24:53.709
-YEAH, RIGHT OVER HERE.

24:55.276 --> 24:56.451
-RIGHT THERE.
-ALL RIGHT.

25:01.804 --> 25:03.284
-HOBIE!

25:05.068 --> 25:08.594
-I'M JUST GONNA TEACH DAD'S
FRIEND HOW TO DO A 360!

25:08.724 --> 25:10.944
-ALL RIGHT. I'LL SEE YOU
AT HEADQUARTERS!

25:11.074 --> 25:12.336
-YEAH, SURE!
-OKAY.

25:12.467 --> 25:13.512
-BYE.

25:20.431 --> 25:22.564
-DAMMIT, GARNER,
I DON'T HAVE ANY PROOF!

25:22.695 --> 25:24.958
BUT I'M TELLING YOU HE WAS
IN MY HOUSE AND HE TOOK
THAT PICTURE OF HOBIE.

25:26.960 --> 25:28.614
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
"TAKE IT EASY"?

25:28.744 --> 25:29.919
I'M WOUND SO TIGHT HERE,
I'M ABOUT READY TO EXPLODE.

25:30.877 --> 25:32.400
YES.

25:32.531 --> 25:34.881
YES, I KNOW THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT HE WANTS ME TO DO.

25:36.186 --> 25:37.144
OKAY.

25:37.971 --> 25:40.800
OKAY, I'LL SIT TIGHT
TILL I HEAR SOMETHING FROM YOU.

25:44.194 --> 25:45.326
HOBIE.

25:47.676 --> 25:48.634
-HI!
-HI.

25:48.764 --> 25:50.070
-WHAT'S YOUR HURRY?

25:50.200 --> 25:52.420
-UH, JUNIOR LIFEGUARDS
JUST FINISHED.

25:52.551 --> 25:53.334
I WANNA MAKE SURE THAT HOBIE'S
NOT WAITING AROUND, YOU KNOW,
ON HIS OWN.

25:54.248 --> 25:56.032
-YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY.

25:56.163 --> 25:57.556
-I JUST SAW HIM BOOGIE
BOARDING WITH THAT FRIEND
OF YOURS.

25:57.686 --> 25:59.819
-WHO?

25:59.949 --> 26:00.863
-THE ASIAN GUY THAT YOU WERE
TALKING TO AT THE RESTAURANT
YESTERDAY.

26:01.864 --> 26:02.952
-GUY'S AFTER HOBIE.

26:03.083 --> 26:05.825
-[TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

26:11.004 --> 26:11.961
HOBIE!

26:12.701 --> 26:14.137
COME ON, HOBIE!
GET OUT OF THE WATER!

26:18.533 --> 26:19.665
HOBIE, COME ON!

26:20.840 --> 26:23.277
-DAD, I WAS JUST TRYING TO TEACH
YOUR FRIEND HOW TO BOOGIE BOARD.

26:23.407 --> 26:25.061
-GO GET ON SHORE
RIGHT NOW!

26:29.239 --> 26:30.893
-YOU'RE OUT OF CONTROL,
BEACH BOY!

26:37.552 --> 26:38.422
-COOL IT!

26:38.553 --> 26:39.598
-CUT IT OUT!

26:41.382 --> 26:42.818
-YOU TOOK THAT PHOTO!

26:42.949 --> 26:44.385
-IT'S NOT WORTH IT!
-STAY OUT OF MY LIFE!

26:44.515 --> 26:46.169
STAY AWAY FROM MY SON!
-COME ON, MITCH.

26:46.300 --> 26:48.868
-YOU'RE BOTH WITNESSES.
HE HIT ME FOR NO REASON.

26:50.609 --> 26:51.479
-LET ME GO.
-COME ON.

26:53.786 --> 26:54.700
COME ON!

27:00.096 --> 27:02.751
-HOW MANY TIMES HAVE I TOLD YOU
NOT TO TALK TO STRANGERS, HUH?

27:03.360 --> 27:05.188
-HE SAID HE WAS A FRIEND--

27:05.319 --> 27:06.625
-HE'S NOT A FRIEND!
HE'S ANYTHING BUT A FRIEND!

27:09.192 --> 27:10.193
-I'M SORRY.

27:10.672 --> 27:13.457
-YOU'RE ALL WITNESSES.
YOU SAW WHAT HAPPENED.

27:13.588 --> 27:15.155
HE HIT ME FOR NO REASON.

27:22.510 --> 27:24.033
-I'M SORRY, PAL.

27:28.211 --> 27:29.604
-SOME LIFEGUARD.

27:35.218 --> 27:37.220
-I WAS HOPING HE WAS JUST
TRYING TO SCARE ME.

27:38.744 --> 27:40.006
BUT I DON'T KNOW ANYMORE.

27:42.051 --> 27:44.401
ALL I'M SAYING TO YOU
IS JUST BE REAL CAREFUL,
WILL YOU?

27:47.143 --> 27:50.103
-BUT IF HE BROKE INTO OUR HOUSE
AND CUT UP OUR PICTURES,

27:51.582 --> 27:53.106
WHY CAN'T WE GET HIM ARRESTED?

27:53.715 --> 27:54.760
BECAUSE WE CAN'T PROVE IT.

27:55.456 --> 27:57.371
-THERE MUST BE SOMETHING
THAT YOU CAN DO, MITCH.

27:57.501 --> 27:59.025
-THIS GUY'S REAL CLEVER, KAYE.

27:59.721 --> 28:02.898
HE KNOWS HOW TO STAY ONE STEP
AHEAD OF THE LAW WITHOUT
BREAKING IT.

28:04.247 --> 28:05.466
OR GETTING CAUGHT
BREAKING IT.

28:07.250 --> 28:08.817
-[PHONE RINGS]

28:17.260 --> 28:18.392
HELLO?

28:20.611 --> 28:21.874
YEAH, GARNER,
HOW ARE YOU?

28:24.137 --> 28:25.007
YEAH.

28:27.531 --> 28:28.707
YEAH, I DID THAT.

28:30.273 --> 28:31.144
WHAT?

28:32.188 --> 28:33.320
OH, COME ON!

28:35.931 --> 28:37.672
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

28:38.934 --> 28:39.935
KAYE?

28:44.244 --> 28:45.941
WOULD YOU MIND HANGING HERE
WITH HOBIE FOR A WHILE?

28:46.072 --> 28:47.551
I GOTTA GO DOWNTOWN.
-SURE.

28:48.074 --> 28:49.249
WHAT DID GARNER
HAVE TO SAY?

28:50.641 --> 28:52.295
SATO'S PRESSING CHARGES.

28:53.949 --> 28:55.864
HOBESTER, I'M GONNA LEAVE
KAYE HERE WITH YOU
FOR A WHILE.

28:55.995 --> 28:56.822
YOU BE GOOD, HUH?

28:56.952 --> 28:58.171
-OKAY.

28:58.998 --> 28:59.912
-THANKS.

29:06.440 --> 29:08.529
-HOW ABOUT US BUILD A FIRE
IN THE FIREPLACE?

29:08.659 --> 29:10.226
-SURE.
-OKAY.

29:12.838 --> 29:13.969
-BEAT THIS.
-ALL RIGHT.

29:14.100 --> 29:15.754
THE QUEEN BEATS THE JACK,

29:15.884 --> 29:17.277
THAT MEANS FIVE,
YOU WON.

29:17.407 --> 29:18.974
I DON'T LIKE THIS GAME ANYMORE.

29:19.670 --> 29:20.715
HOW ABOUT A DESSERT?

29:20.846 --> 29:21.760
-SURE.

29:22.673 --> 29:23.718
-DO YOU HAVE ANY OTHER GAMES?

29:24.458 --> 29:26.112
-MOUSETRAP. ME AND DAD
PLAY IT ALL THE TIME.

29:26.242 --> 29:28.810
-ALL RIGHT, YOU'D PROBABLY
BEAT ME AT THAT ONE, TOO.

29:30.116 --> 29:32.466
-I'M GONNA GO UPSTAIRS
AND GET IT.
-ALL RIGHT.

29:44.826 --> 29:48.264
-[DOG BARKING]

30:24.300 --> 30:26.172
[DOG BARKING CONTINUES]

30:55.157 --> 30:56.202
-HOBIE?

31:03.600 --> 31:04.514
HOBIE?

31:10.216 --> 31:12.087
-[GASPS]

31:14.873 --> 31:17.397
-I THINK THE THREE OF US
SHOULD SPEND SOME TIME TOGETHER.

31:29.975 --> 31:31.977
-MITCH, THEY WENT EASY ON YOU
BECAUSE IT WAS A FIRST OFFENSE.

31:32.107 --> 31:33.239
BUT, I GOTTA TELL YOU...

31:33.369 --> 31:34.022
-I KNOW.
-IF YOU LOSE IT AGAIN--

31:34.153 --> 31:35.328
-I KNOW, OKAY?!

31:36.329 --> 31:37.765
HE JUST PUSHED ME
TOO FAR.

31:37.896 --> 31:39.201
-HE KNEW EXACTLY WHAT
HE WAS DOING, MITCH.

31:39.332 --> 31:40.855
HIS WIFE LEFT TOWN
WITHOUT A TRACE.

31:40.986 --> 31:42.770
WITHOUT HER, WE DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO GET HIM ON.

31:42.901 --> 31:44.293
-ANYTHING YET.

31:44.424 --> 31:46.165
-MITCH, YOU HAVE GOT
TO KEEP YOUR COOL, MAN!

31:46.295 --> 31:47.993
DON'T GIVE HIM ANY MORE POWER
THAN HE ALREADY HAS.

31:48.123 --> 31:49.559
-THIS GUY'S GONNA SLIP UP, PAL.

31:49.690 --> 31:51.126
AND WHEN HE DOES,
I'M GONNA NAIL HIM.

31:51.257 --> 31:52.998
I'M GONNA NAIL HIM PERMANENTLY.

32:22.418 --> 32:23.289
HOBIE?

32:24.855 --> 32:25.726
KAYE?

32:58.063 --> 33:00.891
-YOU KNOW, THERE IS ONE THING
THAT YOUR BEACH BOY AND I
HAVE IN COMMON.

33:03.851 --> 33:05.592
GREAT TASTE IN WOMEN.

33:06.462 --> 33:07.507
-LET THE BOY GO

33:08.421 --> 33:10.118
AND I'LL DO ANYTHING YOU WANT.

33:10.727 --> 33:12.120
-I KNOW YOU WANT
TO BE ALONE WITH ME.

33:12.642 --> 33:14.209
BUT THAT'S GONNA HAVE TO WAIT
TILL LATER.

33:17.038 --> 33:18.561
-DON'T HURT HER,
OR MY DAD WILL KILL YOU.

33:19.693 --> 33:20.563
I SWEAR.

33:31.139 --> 33:32.140
-HE'S GONNA GET THAT CHANCE.

33:34.316 --> 33:36.710
UNLESS, OF COURSE,
I KILL HIM FIRST.

33:47.373 --> 33:49.070
-IT'S GONNA BE OKAY, HOBIE.

33:49.592 --> 33:51.464
JUST HANG ON.
WE'LL GET OUT OF HERE.

33:52.552 --> 33:53.596
-MITCH, HOBIE?

34:05.695 --> 34:07.132
-[ENGINE REVVING]

34:07.262 --> 34:09.569
[TIRES SQUEALING]

34:36.813 --> 34:38.685
[GRUNTING]

35:04.928 --> 35:06.191
-HUAH!

35:36.177 --> 35:37.222
-YOU OKAY?

35:38.745 --> 35:40.399
-DAD!
-IT'S SO GOOD TO SEE YOU!

35:42.009 --> 35:43.097
-AAH!

35:46.709 --> 35:49.364
THIS IS FOR MY SON
AND EVERYTHING YOU TOOK
FROM ME.

36:50.991 --> 36:52.688
-HUAH!

38:14.770 --> 38:15.597
-OH, GARNER!

38:16.642 --> 38:17.860
-ARE YOU OKAY?

38:17.991 --> 38:19.253
-YEAH, BUT WE GOTTA
FIND MY DAD.

38:55.898 --> 38:58.814
[SIRENS APPROACHING]

39:17.355 --> 39:19.574
-YOU SHOULD HAVE KILLED ME
WHEN YOU HAD THE CHANCE.

39:20.270 --> 39:21.184
-NO.

39:22.925 --> 39:23.796
TOO EASY.

39:26.276 --> 39:29.279
-[COUGHING]

39:29.889 --> 39:31.194
-COME ON, WE'LL TAKE IT
FROM HERE.

39:31.325 --> 39:32.457
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

39:36.939 --> 39:37.810
-HEY.

39:37.940 --> 39:39.377
-OH, YOU'RE ALL RIGHT!

39:41.422 --> 39:43.381
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
-YEAH, I'M OKAY.

39:44.773 --> 39:45.600
-DAD!

40:01.616 --> 40:03.401
-ETA TO STATION 10 MINUTES.

40:25.466 --> 40:27.555
-NOW EVERYTHING'S
BACK TO NORMAL.

40:27.686 --> 40:29.644
-[BELL RINGING]

40:30.645 --> 40:32.168
-DINNER IS SERVED.

40:33.648 --> 40:35.737
PLEASE, BE SEATED.

40:35.868 --> 40:39.001
THIS EVENING I WILL BE SERVING
THE MITCH BUCHANNON
EXTRAVAGANZA.

40:39.132 --> 40:40.873
-SIGNORINA.
-THANK YOU.

40:41.003 --> 40:41.874
-IL RAGAZZO.

40:44.006 --> 40:44.920
BUON APPETITO!

40:45.791 --> 40:48.141
-DAD, YOU REALLY KICKED OUT
THE JAMS ON THIS DINNER.

40:48.663 --> 40:51.013
-NOTHING'S EVEN BURNT.
-VERY FUNNY.

40:51.797 --> 40:53.233
-LOOKS REALLY DELICIOUS.

40:53.755 --> 40:55.278
HOW DID YOU DO THIS?

40:55.409 --> 40:57.890
-WELL, I JUST DUG UP SOME OLD
FAMILY RECIPES,

40:58.412 --> 40:59.805
WENT DOWN TO A LITTLE
GOURMET MARKET,

40:59.935 --> 41:01.937
SHOPPED TILL I DROPPED,

41:02.068 --> 41:03.765
SLAVED ALL DAY IN THE KITCHEN,

41:03.896 --> 41:05.550
AND VOILA!

41:06.594 --> 41:08.727
-ALL I CAN SAY IS,
"WHAT'S FOR DESSERT?"

41:08.857 --> 41:11.164
-I HAVE HOMEMADE CHOCOLATE
MOUSE CHEESECAKE IN
THE REFRIGERATOR.

41:11.294 --> 41:12.600
-ARE YOU KIDDING?

41:12.731 --> 41:13.688
-RIVALS YOUR BROWNIES.

41:14.297 --> 41:16.386
-[KNOCKING AT THE DOOR]
-WHAT?

41:16.517 --> 41:20.086
-OH, MR. BUCHANNON, I'M SO SORRY
INTERRUPT YOUR BEAUTIFUL
DINNER HERE,

41:20.216 --> 41:22.784
BUT YOU CANNOT SERVE
MY CHICKEN MARSALA

41:22.915 --> 41:24.307
WITHOUT THE SPECIAL SAUCE.

41:24.438 --> 41:25.570
-IGNORE THAT MAN
WITH THE SAUCE.

41:25.700 --> 41:27.180
-WHO IS THIS GUY?

41:27.310 --> 41:29.225
-I'M NO GUY. I'M VITO,

41:29.356 --> 41:30.662
CATERING YOUR HOME.

41:32.794 --> 41:34.796
YOU NEED TO EAT-O,
CALL VITO!

41:35.928 --> 41:37.277
OH, AND MR. BUCHANNON.
-WHAT?

41:37.407 --> 41:38.800
-ABOUT 30 MINUTES,

41:38.931 --> 41:41.368
THEN THE CHEESECAKE
SHALL BE PERFETTO!

41:45.111 --> 41:46.373
[CHUCKLES]

41:46.504 --> 41:48.418
SLAVED ALL DAY
IN THE KITCHEN, HUH DAD?

41:48.549 --> 41:50.638
AND YOU SHOPPED
TILL YOU DROPPED?

41:50.769 --> 41:51.683
WELL...

41:52.466 --> 41:55.208
WHEN YOU NEED TO EAT-O,
YOU CALL VITO.

41:56.601 --> 41:57.471
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL THING.

41:57.602 --> 41:58.907
[LAUGHING]

42:05.871 --> 42:08.395
[END THEME PLAYS]
